#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:261
msgid ""
"`vtkMergeVectorComponents` has been added to the `VTK::FiltersGeneral` "
"module which supports `vtkDataSet` objects and may be used to combine three "
"arrays of components into a new output array. This filter supports "
"multithreading via `vtkSMPTools`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:265
msgid ""
"`vtkArrowSource` now has an option to be placed and oriented around its "
"center which makes placing it after scaling and rotation much easier."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:267
msgid ""
"`vtkDataSetSurfaceFilter` can now extract surfaces from all structured data "
"sets including `vtkImageData`, `vtkStructuredGrid`, and `vtkRectilinearGrid` "
"when they have blanked cells marked using a ghost array."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:270
msgid ""
"`vtkDataSetSurfaceFilter` has a \"fast mode\" which only considers the outer-"
"most surface without considering external faces within the outer shell which "
"is intended for rendering purposes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:273
msgid ""
"`vtkExtractExodusGlobalTemporalVariables` now supports field data arrays."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:274
msgid ""
"`vtkExtractEdges` now supports a `UseAllPoints` to use a non-`Locator`-based "
"strategy to skip selecting only the points which are used and instead "
"assumes that all points will be present in the output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:277
msgid ""
"The `vtkGhostCellsGenerator` filter is now available to generate ghost "
"cells. It uses DIY for MPI communication internally and can handle any "
"`vtkMultiBlockDataSet`, `vtkPartitionedDataSet`, and "
"`vtkPartitionedDataSetCollection` that is filled with the supported input "
"dataset types including `vtkImageData`, `vtkRectilinearGrid`, "
"`vtkStructuredGrid`, `vtkUnstructuredGrid`, and `vtkPolyData`. Ghost cells "
"are only exchanged with elements of the same type and are treated as the "
"\"closest\" supported common ancestor class. Note that `vtkHyperTreeGrid` is "
"not supported and `vtkHyperTreeGridGhostCellsGenerator` should be used for "
"it instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:287
msgid ""
"`vtkGroupDataSetsFilter` may be used to combine input datasets into a "
"`vtkMultiBlockDataSet`, `vtkPartitionedDataSet`, or "
"`vtkPartitionedDataSetCollection`. Each input is added as an individual "
"block and may be named using `SetInputName`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:291
msgid ""
"`vtkGroupTimeStepsFilter` may be used to turn temporal data into a single "
"`vtkMultiBlockDataSet` or `vtkPartitionedDataSetCollection` with all of the "
"temporal data. The output type is `vtkPartitionedDataSetCollection` unless "
"the input is `vtkMultiBlockDataSet` in which case another "
"`vtkMultiBlockDataSet` is output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:296
msgid ""
"`vtkVortexCore`'s output points now include interpolated variables of the "
"input points."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:298
msgid "`vtkVortexCore` is now fully multithreaded using `vtkSMPTools`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:299
msgid ""
"`vtkMergeTimeFilter` may be used to synchronize multiple input temporal "
"datasets. The output is a `vtkMultiBlockDataSet` with one block per input "
"element. The output timestep may be either a union or intersection of the "
"input timestep lists (which may be de-duplicated with either absolute or "
"relative tolerances)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:304
msgid ""
"`vtkResizingWindowToImageFilter` may be used as an alternative to "
"`vtkWindowToImageFilter` to create screenshots of any size and aspect ratio "
"using the `SetSize(width, height)` method regardless of the window size. "
"Note that offscreen buffers are used and therefore memory usage is higher "
"than `vtkWindowToImageFilter`. Memory usage may be limited using the "
"`SetSizeLimit(width, height)` method (defaulting to `(4000, 4000)`). For "
"images larger than the limit the filter will fallback to "
"`vtkWindowToImageFilter` in order to save memory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:312
msgid ""
"`vtkExtractVectorComponents` can now work multithreaded using `vtkSMPTools`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:313
msgid ""
"`vtkPartitionedDataSetCollectionSource` is now available to programmatically "
"produce a `vtkPartitionedDataSetCollection`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:315
msgid ""
"`vtkThresholdPoints::InputArrayComponent` has been added to enable selection "
"of a single component within the active data array. If a value larger than "
"the number of components is used, the magnitude of each array tuple will be "
"used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:319
msgid ""
"`vtkTubeBender` is now provided in order to generate better paths for tubes "
"in `vtkTubeFilter`. This is particularly visible when generating tubes "
"around acute angles."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:322
msgid "`vtkArrayCalculator` now supports multithreading via `vtkSMPTools`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:323
msgid ""
"`vtkVectorFieldTopology` may be used to compute the topological skeleton of "
"a 2D or 3D vector field given as a set of critical points and separatrices. "
"Separatrices are lines in 2D and surfaces in 3D (computed via "
"`vtkStreamSurface`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:327
msgid "`vtkTableFFT` now offers a frequency column in the output table."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:328
msgid ""
"`vtkTableFFT` can now compute the FFT per block and then average these "
"results."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:330
msgid ""
"`vtkTableFFT` can now apply a windowing function before computing the FFT."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:331
msgid "`vtkMergeCells` can now merge points using double precision tolerances."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:332
msgid ""
"`vtkTemporalPathLineFilter` can now manage backwards times using its "
"`SetBackwardTime()` method. When using backwards time, each `vtkDataObject::"
"DATA_TIME_STEP()` from subsequent `::RequestData()` method calls will "
"decrease."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:336
msgid ""
"`vtkPlaneCutter` used to always generate a vtkMultiBlockDataSet regardless "
"of input type. Now `vtkPlaneCutter` decides what the output type will be "
"based on the input type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:339
msgid ""
"If input type is `vtkUniformGridAMR` or `vtkMultiBlockDataSet`, the output "
"type will be `vtkMultiBlockDataSet`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:341
msgid ""
"If input type is `vtkPartitionedDataSetCollection`, the output type will be "
"`vtkPartitionedDataSetCollection`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:343
msgid ""
"If input type is `vtkDataSet` or `vtkPartitionedDataSet`, the output type "
"will be `vtkPartitionedDataSet`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:345
msgid ""
"The `RemapPointIds` functor of `vtkRemoveUnusedPoints` has now been "
"multithreaded properly. (#18222)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:348
msgid "<a name=\"imaging\"></a>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:348
msgid "<a name=\"imaging\">"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:349
msgid "Imaging {#imaging}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:351
msgid ""
"The `vtkImageProbeFilter` works like `vtkProbeFilter`, but is designed for "
"image data. It uses `vtkImageInterpolator` rather than cell and point "
"interpolations. The filter supports SMP acceleration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:358
msgid ""
"VTK can now read ADIOS2 files or data streams using [Fides][fides]. This can "
"be provided as a JSON file containing the data model or Fides can generate "
"its own data model automatically (see Fides documentation for details). "
"Fides converts the ADIOS2 data to a VTK-m dataset and the `vtkFidesReader` "
"creates partitioned datasets that contain either native VTK datasets or VTK "
"VTK-m datasets. Time and time streaming is supported. Note that the "
"interface for time streaming is different and requires calling "
"`PrepareNextStep()` and `Update()` for each new step."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:366
msgid ""
"The `vtkCONVERGECFDReader` has been added to read CONVERGE CFD (version 3.1) "
"files containing meshes, surfaces, and parcels as well as support for time "
"series data. Each stream is considered its own block. Cell and point data "
"arrays may be selected using the `CellArrayStatus` and `ParcelArrayStatus` "
"APIs. Note that parallel support is not yet available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:371
msgid ""
"`vtkEnSightGoldBinaryReader` now supports reading undefined and partial "
"variables from per-node and per-element files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:373
msgid ""
"VTK's EnSight Gold support can now read asymmetric tensors. This is not "
"supported in EnSight6 files yet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:375
msgid ""
"The `vtkIossReader` has been added which supports reading CGNS and Exodus "
"databases and files. The output is provided as a "
"`vtkPartitionedDataSetCollection` with `vtkDataAssembly` representing the "
"logical structure. Note that not all CGNS files are supported; only the "
"subset supported by the backing [IOSS library][ioss]. Eventually, the "
"`vtkExodusIIReader` will be deprecated in preference for this reader."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:381
msgid ""
"The `vtkMP4Writer` writer may be used to write H.264-encoded MP4 files on "
"Windows using the Microsoft Media Foundation API. The `Rate` property is "
"available to set the framerate and the `BitRate` property may be used to set "
"the quality of the output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:385
msgid ""
"`vtkOMFReader` may be used to read [Open Mining Format][open-mining-format] "
"files. The output is a `vtkPartitionedDataSetCollection` with each "
"`vtkPartitionedDataSet` is one OMF element (point set, line set, surface, or "
"volume)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:389
msgid ""
"`vtkOpenVDBWriter` may be used to write [OpenVDB][openvdb] files. MPI is "
"supported by writing separate files for each rank. Temporal data is also "
"written to a separate file for each timestep."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:392
msgid "`vtkTGAReader` may be used to read TGA images."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:393
msgid "`vtkPDBReader` now supports reading PDB files with multiple models."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:394
msgid ""
"`vtkPDBReader` now generates an array containing the model each atom belongs "
"to."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:396
msgid "`vtkVelodyneReader` may be used to read Velodyne AMR files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:398
msgid "![AMR-Detonation](imgs/9.1/AMRDetonationVelodyne.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:398
msgid "AMR-Detonation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:400
msgid "`vtkNrrdReader` can now read gzip-encoded compressed NRRD files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:401
msgid "`vtkOpenFOAMReader` now supports reading internal dimensioned fields."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:402
msgid ""
"`vtkOpenFOAMReader` now supports string expansion syntaxes from OpenFOAM "
"v1806 (`#include`, `<case>`, `<constant>`, `<system>`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:404
msgid ""
"`vtkOpenFOAMReader` now handles mixed-precision workflows much more robustly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:405
msgid ""
"`vtkOpenFOAMReader` now handles multi-region cases without a default region."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:406
msgid ""
"`vtkOpenFOAMReader` now respects the `inGroups` boundary entry for selection "
"of multiple patches by group."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:408
msgid ""
"`vtkOpenFOAMReader` now properly handles empty zones and has basic support "
"for face zones."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:410
msgid ""
"`vtkOpenFOAMReader` respects point patch value fields using the correct "
"visitation order."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:412
msgid "`vtkOpenFOAMReader` no longer has hard-coded limits on polyhedral size."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:413
msgid "`vtkOpenFOAMReader` now preserves uncollated Lagrangian information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:414
msgid ""
"`vtkOpenFOAMReader` now avoids naming ambiguities for Lagrangian and region "
"names using a `/regionName/` prefix for non-default regions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:422
msgid "<a name=\"interaction\"></a>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:422
msgid "<a name=\"interaction\">"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:423
msgid "Interaction {#interaction}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:425
msgid ""
"A new 3D camera orientation widget. The widget's representation is "
"synchronized with the camera of the owning renderer. The widget may be used "
"to select an axis or using its handles."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:428
msgid ""
"`vtkSelectionNode` now supports `BLOCK_SELECTORS` to select whole blocks "
"from a composite dataset using a selector expression for hierarchy or an "
"associated `vtkDataAssembly` for `vtkPartitionedDataSetCollection`s."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:431
msgid ""
"Interactive 2D widgets have been added (ported from ParaView). The "
"`vtkEqualizerFilter` and `vtkEqualizerContextItem` are now available using "
"this feature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:434
msgid ""
"Source data: ![Equalizer filter and Interactive 2D](imgs/9.1/"
"interactive_2d_before.png \"Equalizer filter\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:434
#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:435
msgid "Equalizer filter and Interactive 2D"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:435
msgid ""
"After applying the filter: ![Equalizer filter and Interactive 2D](imgs/9.1/"
"interactive_2d_after.png \"Equalizer filter\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:436
msgid ""
"VTK's OpenVR's input model has been updated to be action-based and supports "
"binding customization within the OpenVR user interface. This includes "
"controller labeling and user configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:439
msgid ""
"`vtkEventData` now understands an \"Any\" device so that handlers can look "
"for all events and do filtering internally. See [merge request 7557][vtk-"
"mr7557] for an example of how to update custom 3D event handling."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:442
msgid "`vtkResliceCursorWidget` now refreshes when scrolling."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:443
msgid ""
"Frustum selection of lines and polylines now only considers the line itself, "
"not their containing area (i.e., they were treated as polygons during "
"selection)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:446
msgid ""
"Selections of `vtkDataAssembly` may be limited to a subset of blocks using a "
"collection of xpath selectors for the dataset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:448
msgid "`vtkChartXYZ` can now be controlled using the arrow keys for rotation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:449
msgid ""
"`vtkScalarBarActor` now supports custom tick locations via "
"`vtkScalarBarActor::SetCustomLabels()` and `vtkScalarBarActor::"
"SetUseCustomLabels()`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:458
msgid "Java 1.7 is now required (bumped from 1.6)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:459
msgid ""
"The wrapped Java API now handles strings more efficiently by handling "
"encoding in the Java wrappers directly. No APIs are affected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:465
msgid ""
"`vtkPythonInterpreter::SetRedirectOutput` can be used to disable Python "
"output to `vtkOutputWindow`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:467
msgid ""
"VTK now offers two CMake options for deployments that can help to handle "
"Python 3.8's DLL loading policy changes on Windows. This allows `import "
"vtkmodules` to handle `PATH` manipulations to ensure VTK can be loaded "
"rather than relying on `vtkpython` to do this work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:471
msgid ""
"`VTK_UNIFIED_INSTALL_TREE`: This option can be set to indicate that VTK will "
"share an install tree with its dependencies. This allows VTK to avoid doing "
"extra work that doesn't need to be done in such a situation. This is ignored "
"if `VTK_RELOCATABLE_INSTALL` is given (there's no difference there as VTK "
"assumes that how VTK is used in such a case is handled by other means)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:477
msgid ""
"`VTK_DLL_PATHS`: A list of paths to give to Python to use when loading DLL "
"libraries."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:479
msgid ""
"Python wrappers will now generate deprecation warnings when the underlying "
"VTK API is deprecated. Since Python silences `DeprecationWarning` by "
"default, the warnings must be allowed via:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:483
msgid ""
"import warnings\n"
"warnings.filterwarnings(\"default\", category=DeprecationWarning)\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:488
msgid ""
"With Python 3.6 and newer, VTK APIs marked with attributes that indicate "
"that paths are expected will now support `pathlike` objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:490
msgid ""
"Wrapped Python APIs now contain docstrings with type hints as described in "
"[PEP 484][pep-484]. This will help with IDE tab completion and hinting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:492
msgid ""
"VTK's `vtkmodules` package and `vtk` module now provide `__version__` "
"attributes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:494
msgid ""
"The `vtkmodules.web.render_window_serializer` module may be used to "
"additionally serialize `vtkPolyData`, `vtkImageData`, and `mergeToPolyData` "
"optionally using the `requested_fields=['*']` argument."
msgstr ""

