msgid "<a name=\"qt\"></a>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:500
msgid "<a name=\"qt\">"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:501
msgid "Qt {#qt}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:503
msgid ""
"VTK now supports Qt6 using the `VTK_QT_VERSION` variable. This may be set to "
"`Auto` in which case the first of Qt6 or Qt5 found will be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:505
msgid ""
"The `VTK::GUISupportQtQuick` module has been added which supports the "
"necessary integration classes as well as the QML module infrastructure "
"required to import VTK into a QtQuick application."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:512
msgid ""
"The `vtkOutlineGlowRenderPass` renders a scene as a glowing outline. "
"Combined with layered renderers this creates a very visible highlight "
"without altering the highlighted object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:515
msgid ""
"VisRTX and OptiX now offer trace-level debugging information to determine "
"why they may not be available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:517
msgid ""
"`vtkMultiBlockUnstructuredGridVolumeMapper` has been added to volume render "
"the entirety of a multi-block unstructured grid without merging them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:519
msgid ""
"The physical-based render shader now supports anisotropic materials. This "
"may be modified using the `Anisotropy` and `AnisotropyRotation` properties. "
"Support for these values from a texture is also available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:522
msgid ""
"`vtkBlockItem` may now resize itself based on the label specified. "
"Additionally, options for the brush, pen, and text, padding, margins are "
"available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:525
msgid "Multi-volume ray-casting now supports shading."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:526
msgid ""
"`vtkMatplotlibMathTextUtilities` now supports multi-line (using `\\n`) and "
"multi-column (using `|` separators) text. `vtkTextProperty` now has a "
"`CellOffset` property to control the spaces between columns (in pixels)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:529
msgid ""
"The GPU-based ray-casting volume mapper now supports rendering non-uniform "
"rectilinear grids. Volume streaming via block partitioning is not yet "
"supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:533
msgid ""
"![Rectilinear-Grid-Volume](imgs/9.1/TestGPURayCastMapperRectilinearGrid.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:533
msgid "Rectilinear-Grid-Volume"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:535
msgid ""
"`vtkOpenGLMovieSphere` may be used to display spherical movies using OpenGL. "
"Both regular 360° video and stereo 360° video is supported where stereo "
"streams are split into left and right eye rendering passes. The video is "
"sent to the graphics card as YUV textures which are decoded to RGB in the "
"associated shaders."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:540
msgid "VTK's VisRTX support is now compatible with OSPRay 2.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:541
msgid ""
"The OpenGL `vtkPolyData` mappers now provide a way to handle jitter "
"introduced by rendering with single-precision vertex coordinates far from "
"the origin. The `PauseShiftScale` parameter may be used to suspend updates "
"during user interactions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:545
msgid ""
"`vtkResliceCursorRepresentation::BoundPlane()` is now offered to show the "
"entire resliced image when rotating."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:547
msgid ""
"`vtkOpenGLPolyDataMapper` now supports a `vtkSelection` object to display "
"selected ids or values directly from the mapper itself. Selections are "
"rendered in a second pass as a wireframe using the `vtkProperty::"
"SelectionColor` color."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:551
msgid ""
"The GPU-based ray-casting volume mapper now supports direct volume rendering "
"with the blanking of cells and points defined by individual ghost arrays."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:553
msgid "Uniform grid with blanking:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:555
msgid ""
"![Uniform-Grid-Blanking](imgs/9.1/TestGPURayCastVolumeUniformGridBlanking."
"png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.1-stripped.md:555
msgid "Uniform-Grid-Blanking"
msgstr ""

